sec.p:
Besides rethinking on the part of the medical profession in the direction of generics, the increasing participation of generic medicines is possible, amongst other things, because German pharmacies are obligated to substitute doctor-prescribed medicines for one of the three cheapest generic medicines (‘aut idem rule’). Requirements for the exchanged medicines are:


the same active ingredient;

the same packet size;

the same dose;

the same pharmaceutical form as the prescribed medicine; and

that the doctor has not excluded the substitution of the prescribed medicine.
